casebody.data:
MISCELLANEOUS DISMISSALS

02-106. Killings v. Gorman.

In Procedendo. On January 22, 2002, relator filed a complaint in procedendo. In lieu of the filing fee required by S.Ct.Prac.R. XV(1), relator tendered an affidavit of indigency. Whereas relator’s affidavit was executed more than one year- ago, it does not meet the requirements of S.Ct.Prac.R. XV(3). Accordingly,

IT IS ORDERED by the court, sua sponte, that the affidavit of indigency be, and hereby is, stricken.

IT IS FURTHER ORDERED by the court that this cause be, and hereby is, dismissed.
